The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                            BRIEFS
                  
	Krishnagar, Jan. 28: A man holding his mobile phone to the ear by his neck while riding his motorcycle was crushed under the wheels of a truck in Nadias Shantipur last night.    
	Agni Mitra, 35, a railway clerk, loved theatre. He was going to Shantipur, where the troupe he directed was based. Police said the truck screeched to a halt after hitting the motorcycle near a market 80km from Calcutta. People realised it was not the drivers fault alone and ensured that he was not beaten up.        
	Calcutta: Union fin- ance minister P. Chidambaram will visit the Sunderbans in mid-February for an assessment of the mangroves tourism potential. The chief minister, who discussed a draft tourism policy on Monday, had requested him to see if the Sunderbans could be developed as a tourist hub.        
	Tamluk: Three passengers were killed when a Digha-Howrah bus overturned near Khejuri in East Midnapore, about 150km from Calcutta.                                                                                                                                                                       
